IDLE = Integrated Development Environment
IDE = Integrated Development Environment (a software aplication that provides comprehensive facilities to computer programmers for software development.
      An IDE normally consists of at least a source code editor, build automation tools and a debugger

IDEs for Python:
- idle
- pycharm
- spyder
- Microsoft Visual Studio
- Eclipse
- PyDev
- Atom
- Thonny
- PyScripter etc

Text editor - a type of program that edits plain text
Text editors for Python:
a8
Alphatk
Bluefish
Cream
Cssed
Crisp
Drakon
